<b>Hi</b>, 
<br/> </br>
My name is <b>Ms. Paredes </b> and I would like to invite you to my 1st grade classroom.  I am very eager to get to know <br/> every one of you. I am looking forward to creating many great memories with all of you. 
<br/><br/>This year is going to be very exciting year. We have some <em>fun </em> field trips planned out for this year and I hope that <br/> everyone can make it. There is also a lot of fun and interesting topics that we will learn about. <br/> <br/>
I would like to share with all of you the topics that we will be learning this year. 
<br/> <br/>

<dl>

<dt>Reading:  </dt> <dd> <p> We will be working on vocabulary, reading comprehension, and letter and word sounds. 
</p>
</dd>

<br/>

<dt> Writing: </dt> <dd> <p> We will be working on leaning important everyday spelling words. In addition to this we will be working on the <br/> different features of writing such as pre-writing, drafting, revising, editing, and publishing. </P>
</dd>


<dt>Math:</dt>  <dd> <p> We will be working on addition and subtraction. We will then be moving into telling time and how to count money.
</p>
</dd>

<br/>

<dt>Social Studies: </dt>  <dd> <p> We will learn about important people in the past and how they used to live. We will also be working with maps and  <br/> identifying important components. 
</p>
</dd>
<br/>

<dt>Science: </dt>  <dd> <p> We will start off the school year with learning about plants. We will then move into matter, and then the rock cycle. 
</p>
</dd>
</dl>
<br/>
I made this website as a resource for you, this way you can learn about my classroom and I.  I believe <em>communication </em>  is  very<br/> important and crucial part  of creating a healthy environment for students.  I hope this website acts as a way of communication <br/> between you and I. I have provided my contact information as well in case of any questions or emergencies.
I plan to keep this <br/> website  updated and current. I will be putting important information on here and any forms or permission slips that you may need. <br/>If you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact me. 

<br/><br/>
<i>Thank you, </i> 

<br/><br/>
<strong>Ms. Paredes</strong>
